						               													<description>This is a game based on 8-bit video game &amp;quot;Battle City&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game players control their tanks on the modular board and strive to destroy bot-tanks and capture the eagle to get victory points. The game is  continious until three eagles were captures or one player scored 5 points more than the next one after him.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player own his deck and takes cards in a hand from it. To perform actions players play cards from hand - so they can rotation and move their tanks.&amp;#10;First, players choose cards for first and second maneuver facedown. It can be any namber of rotation cards, but only one move action.&amp;#10;Now start with the first player and continue the clockwise players perform their first maneuver, then move all the bot-tanks by special rules. When all tanks moved, they shoot on target. Player's tank can shoot on the brick wall or any other tanks. Bot-tanks can shoot only at player's tank. All shoot is simultaneously.&amp;#10;If a player's tank shoot at bot-tank, they is destroy now, and player get a victory point. Now a bonus tile is placed On a battlefield.&amp;#10;If the player's tank is shot, player must discard 2 cards. If he can not, his tank is destroyed until this round ends.&amp;#10;After the first maneuver is performed, players perform second maneuver. After second maneuver a round is ending and players prepare to the next round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summmary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
